Package: somato
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Soma cube animation
 Somato solves and animates Piet Hein's Soma puzzle.
 .
 The Soma cube is a solid dissection puzzle invented by Piet Hein during
 a lecture on quantum mechanics conducted by Werner Heisenberg. Seven
 pieces made out of unit cubes must be assembled into a 3x3x3 cube. The
 pieces of the Soma cube consist of all possible combinations of four or
 fewer unit cubes, excluding all regular shapes.

Package: somato-sse
Architecture: i386
Conflicts: somato
Replaces: somato
Provides: somato
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Soma cube animation [SSE]
 Somato solves and animates Piet Hein's Soma puzzle.
 .
 The Soma cube is a solid dissection puzzle invented by Piet Hein during
 a lecture on quantum mechanics conducted by Werner Heisenberg. Seven
 pieces made out of unit cubes must be assembled into a 3x3x3 cube. The
 pieces of the Soma cube consist of all possible combinations of four or
 fewer unit cubes, excluding all regular shapes.
 .
 This package is optimized for the Intel Pentium III processor with SSE
 (Streaming SIMD Extensions) and will not run on subarchitectures that
 don't support the features enabled by the Pentium III.
